<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Profile Page</title>
    <style>
        body {
            background-color: black;
            color: white;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
        }
        .container {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(12, 1fr);
            grid-template-rows: auto auto;
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 1200px; /* Adjust based on your preference */
            gap: 20px;
        }
        .main-text {
            grid-column: 5 / 9;
            text-align: left;
        }
        .profile-image {
            grid-column: 5 / 6;
            width: 150px;
            height: 150px;
            background-color: white; /* Example, replace with image */
            border-radius: 50%;
            justify-self: start;
        }
        .name-text {
            grid-column: 5 / 9;
            align-self: center;
            text-align: left;
        }
        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .container {
                grid-template-columns: repeat(6, 1fr);
                padding: 10px;
            }
            .main-text, .profile-image, .name-text {
                grid-column: 2 / 6;
            }
            .profile-image {
                justify-self: center;
            }
            .name-text {
                text-align: center;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="main-text">
                <p>
                  This year I volunteered at Govtech’s Girls in Tech program (as a mentor), and got inspired to create this
                  website as some sort of career hunt power tool from the interactions with the ambitious albeit a little
                  anxious young ladies.
                </p>
                <p>I guess this is also a loving homage to my first big girl job in Shanghai with an AI startup
                  (specializing in recruitment solutions) </p>
                <p>Still in search of my “ikigai” - what you love, what you are good at, what you are paid for, and what the
                  world needs.</p>
            </div>
               </div>
        <div class="profile-image">
            <!-- Image would be here -->
        </div>
        <div class="name-text">
            <figure>
                <br><br><br>
                <blockquote class="blockquote">
                  <p>YING HUI TAN</p>
                </blockquote>
                <figcaption class="blockquote-footer">
                  Business Analyst, Govtech (IMDA)
                </figcaption>        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
